description: A crunchy snack and a healthier alternative to traditional chips, make our parsnip chips a great go-to recipe. Easy to make and on the table in 15 minutes.
keywords: Chips & fries,Pescatarian,Low saturated fat,Low salt,Seafood free,Gluten free,Tree nut free,Egg free,Low sugar,Sesame free,Halal,Parsnip,Soy free,Wheat free,Vegetarian,Vegan,Dairy free,Peanut free
name: Parsnip Crisps Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 4 parsnips, washed, cut into strips with a peeler

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 220°C. Toss parsnip with oil and season.
Spread parsnip, in a single layer, on a baking paper-lined tray. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden and crisp.
